article.headline: W. Illinois 71, SE Missouri 66
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Guard David DuBois scored 25 points Wednesday night to lead Western Illinois to a 71-66 come-from-behind victory over Southeast Missouri State. The Leathernecks trailed 27-26 at the half, but erupted for 45 points after intermission to take the win. Western Illinois (4-5), got 16 points from David Nurse, who was 4-for-7 in 3-point attempts, and another 14 from Clark Ceola. Kenard Moore led the Redhawks (2-7) with 20 points, followed by Jaycen Herring with 19. Western Illinois forward James Granstra fouled out with 14 seconds remaining.
